Frontend Guidelines for SmartReno:

Framework:
- Next.js
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS

Frontend Rules:

- Keep components small, readable, and modular
- Separate presentation from business logic
- Prefer existing hooks/services/utils over inline fetch/query logic
- Do not place sensitive logic in the browser if it belongs on the server
- Use typed responses and props
- Keep forms predictable and resilient
- Preserve the existing design system and app patterns where possible

State Management Rules:

- Avoid fragile state logic
- Avoid deeply nested state when simpler composition works
- Prefer clear derived state over duplicated state
- Handle loading, empty, success, and error states explicitly

Error Handling Rules:

- Always show user-friendly errors
- Log developer-useful details where appropriate
- Never silently swallow failures
- Do not expose internal implementation details to end users

Avoid:

- large monolithic components
- direct database writes without established project patterns
- duplicated API logic across pages/components
- unnecessary refactors
- introducing new libraries unless clearly justified

Prefer:

- reusable hooks
- typed service functions
- clear loading indicators
- stable form handling
- incremental UI changes over rewrites

